                    <event ana="http://syriaca.org/keyword/conversion http://syriaca.org/keyword/baptism http://syriaca.org/keyword/anointing http://syriaca.org/keyword/heretics http://syriaca.org/keyword/council-of-ephesus-i-431 http://syriaca.org/keyword/creeds" when="0431">
                        <desc>
                            The Council of Ephesus in 431 heard from 
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2626">Charisius</persName> that many in 
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/1526">Lydia</placeName> followed a creed by 
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/780">Theodore of Mopsuestia</persName>. In rejecting 
                            it and Nestorianism, the Council required only an orthodox profession of faith without the need for 
                            be re-baptism or re-anointing.
                        </desc>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/669"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">299-300</citedRange>
                    <citedRange unit="part">V.6</citedRange>
